<subpara id="RM000000WC101DX_08" type-id="51" category="05" proc-id="RM0250U___00007AE00000">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten4>
<ptxt>Read freeze frame data using the intelligent tester. The ECM records vehicle and driving condition information as freeze frame data the moment a DTC is stored. When troubleshooting, freeze frame data can help determine if the vehicle was moving or stationary, if the engine was warmed up or not, if the air-fuel ratio was lean or rich, and other data from the time the malfunction occurred.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000WC101DX_09" type-id="01" category="01">
<name>PROCEDURE</name>
<testgrp id="RM000000WC101DX_09_0001" proc-id="RM0250U___00007AF00000">
<testtitle>INSPECT AIR-FUEL RATIO SENSOR (HEATER RESISTANCE)</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Disconnect the C15 A/F sensor connector.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="A052607E27" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Measure the resistance between the terminals of the A/F sensor connector.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard resistance</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.07in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.06in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>1 (HA1A) - 2 (+B)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>1.8 Ω to 3.4 Ω at 20°C (68°F)</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>1 (HA1A) - 4 (A1A-)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Reconnect the A/F sensor connector.</ptxt>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000WC101DX_09_0004" fin="false">OK</down>
<right ref="RM000000WC101DX_09_0007" fin="true">NG</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000WC101DX_09_0004" proc-id="RM0250U___00007AH00000">
